&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 data-local-id=&quot;531ee9ad8a11&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;heading&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;0 0 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;mark&quot; data-prosemirror-mark-name=&quot;strong&quot;&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;4074bfaad053&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Our Restaurant Acquisition team is the engine behind DoorDash&#39;s growth across Australia. We identify, pitch, and sign new SMB restaurant partners bringing the best local dining onto the platform and expanding selection for customers in every market we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-local-id=&quot;ebf521ecf25a&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;heading&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;mark&quot; data-prosemirror-mark-name=&quot;strong&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;e57cb28933c8&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;As an Account Executive, you&#39;ll be responsible for acquiring our new SMB restaurant partners for DoorDash. You&#39;ll own the full sales cycle: from prospecting and outreach to pitching, negotiating, and signing, building a strong pipeline of high-quality merchants that fuel marketplace growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;ffbe07fd6b23&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Working cross-functionally with Marketing, Operations, Customer Success and Strategy teams, you&#39;ll leverage market insights and competitive intelligence to win in your territory and convert top prospects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-local-id=&quot;df830e128ff8&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Please note: this is a highly field-based role requiring regional and interstate travel (including overnight travel and occasional week-long trips). Candidates must hold a valid full driver’s licence and be comfortable with travel requirements that may vary based on business priorities and market needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-local-id=&quot;23f6421c83de&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;heading&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;mark&quot; data-prosemirror-mark-name=&quot;strong&quot;&gt;You&#39;re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-local-id=&quot;728c6cf499f9&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Hunt and close new restaurant partners: pitch and sign SMB restaurants from iconic local favourites to exciting up-and-coming venues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-local-id=&quot;a0403f072ca4&quot; data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DoorDash is looking for top-talent to help grow our New Zealand business! We&#39;re looking for passionate individuals with deep market knowledge to allow us to best serve our consumers, Dashers, and merchants. Join our never-ending pursuit to better power economies in New Zealand and across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DoorDash is looking for an Account Manager to join the New Verticals Partnerships team, to help promote and execute the strategy for our partnerships in our convenience, retail and grocery vertical. Given the scale of our partners, you will be an essential piece of DoorDash&#39;s success in New Zealand. As an Account Manager on the Partnerships Team you&#39;ll help execute growth plans, improve quality, and deliver data insights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re excited about this opportunity because...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with New Vertical&amp;nbsp; partners to grow sales, improve quality, and deliver data insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally and serve as the liaison between our partners and DoorDash teams, particularly with our growth, merchandising, marketing, and operations teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute a growth strategy across our convenience, retail and grocery partners, including large scale growth initiatives as well as tactical, targeted campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee partner specific needs (e.g., POS (point of sale) integrations, customised reporting, catalogue optimisation, merchant marketing, operational improvements)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build direct relationships with important partners throughout each partner, ensuring client needs are met at all levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will report directly to the Enterprise Partnerships Manager, New Zealand&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re excited about you because you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 4 years of experience working in account management, management consulting, project management, client success, and/or sales management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience with data, specifically SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong project management skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Love working directly with clients; you create and&amp;nbsp;maintain long-term relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Know how to take very broad challenges or opportunities and turn them into actionable projects with clear goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About DoorDash&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At DoorDash, our mission to empower local economies shapes how our team members move quickly, learn, and reiterate in order to make impactful decisions that display empathy for our range of users—from Dashers to merchant partners to consumers. We are a technology and logistics company that started by enabling door-to-door delivery, and we are looking for team members who can help us go from a company that is known as the place you order food to a company that people turn to for any and all goods.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;DoorDash is growing rapidly and changing constantly, which gives our team members the opportunity to share their unique perspectives, s

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate to join the Enterprise team. This person will support our Enterprise Account Managers with the day-to-day management, analytics, reporting, and operational execution for some of our largest enterprise restaurant partners across Australia and New Zealand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DoorDash Restaurant Enterprise team is responsible for the strategic vision and development of key restaurant merchants in Australia and New Zealand. DoorDash is a fast-moving company, so we are looking for someone who is adaptable, hard-working, a team player, a critical thinker, organised, and an optimistic problem solver. In this role you will support Enterprise Account Managers through analytics, reporting, operational workstreams, and cross-functional collaboration - turning data into commercial insights that shape how we grow our biggest restaurant partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Analytics &lt;/strong&gt;- Build and own client reporting and dashboards, translating raw data into a clear &quot;so what&quot; that drives commercial decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Insights &lt;/strong&gt;- Produce data-driven analyses, presentations, and recommendations that support business reviews, joint business planning, and commercial renegotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence &lt;/strong&gt;- Drive day-to-day operational workstreams end to end, including menu optimisation, project planning, store onboardings and change of ownerships, merchant marketing, and custom reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Collaboration &lt;/strong&gt;- Partner with product, marketing, operations, and analytics teams to solve problems and keep workstreams moving for our clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Support &lt;/strong&gt;-&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Support Enterprise Account Managers across the management and growth of our top restaurant partners, including preparing for and attending merchant meetings and conferences across Australia and New Zealand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience&lt;/strong&gt; - You have 1-3 years&#39; experience in a fast-paced environment such as management consulting, tech, FMCG, commercial / category management, account management, or analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entrepreneurial&lt;/strong&gt; - You create your own structure in a fast-moving environment; where there&#39;s no playbook, you write one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relationship-builder&lt;/strong&gt; - You love working directly with clients; you create and maintain long-term relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytically rigorous &lt;/strong&gt;- You&#39;re confident in spreadsheets and BI tools, and can turn raw data into a clear, defensible commercial insight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A structured communicator &lt;/strong&gt;- You organise information clearly and make it easy for stakeholders to understand and act on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An owner&lt;/strong&gt; - You m

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Marketplace Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team at DoorDash is responsible for accelerating Marketplace growth, consumer engagement and retention. Using a customer-obsessed approach, we own market strategy, consumer affordability, the end-to-end DoorDash app experience and new value propositions. We are looking for a hands-on builder to optimise how consumers interact with merchants and develop strategies that drive frequency and loyalty.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring an Associate Manager to lead the &lt;strong&gt;NZ marketplace strategy&lt;/strong&gt; and to drive consumer growth in a way that keeps customers coming back. Your work will shape how consumers discover and engage with DoorDash—across merchandising, in-app experience, pricing and partnerships. As this role sits at the intersection of strategy, analytics and cross-functional execution - you will closely partner with Product, Engineering, Sales and Marketing across the Restaurant and New Verticals business lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A core part of the role is leveraging metrics to guide decision-making. You will analyse performance across key levers such as conversion, retention, frequency, and category adoption, translating insights into clear priorities and action plans. You will also contribute to go-to-market and expansion strategies, using data to determine which areas to prioritise and how to scale them effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own and optimise critical aspects of the in-app experience—from how consumers discover merchants and offerings, to how merchandising is executed across the platform. This includes ensuring that the right selection is surfaced to the right customers at the right time, and that the overall journey is seamless, intuitive, and aligned with our growth objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly visible team with fast feedback loops, where ideas quickly turn into live experiences and impact can be seen in real time across consumer engagement, order growth and dollars earned for merchants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report into the Manager on our Consumer Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team. This is a hybrid role, with 3 days in-office (Auckland) and 2 days remote.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategise&lt;/strong&gt; - create and execute the go-to-market strategy for our consumers and merchants, considering in-app engagement, retention and order rates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and execute&lt;/strong&gt; - test and incorporate new product features in collaboration with international product and engineering teams and continually measure performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate daily with a broad team&lt;/strong&gt; - you will lead New Zealand’s in-app experience, partnering with Sales, Marketing, Ads &amp;amp; Promotions teams to ensure Restaurant and New Verticals merchants meet their conversion and impression targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyse and lead &lt;/strong&gt;- use quantitative and qualitative data to inform strategy, prioritize initiatives, define and track KPIs and communicate insights to senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment&lt;/strong&gt; - use a

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Sales Enablement team, under the Sales Strategy &amp;amp; Operations organization, enables the productivity of our sales and go-to-market organizations through alignment with capital OKRs and a 360-degree enablement strategy that encompasses activation across process, product, skill, GTM strategy and tooling. Through partnerships with Sales, Product, Marketing, and Operations, we design and deliver critical enablement programs that activate the business to drive sales performance and contribute to DoorDash’s overall success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Manager of Sales Enablement focused on our Australia and New Zealand (ANZ) markets, you will play a critical role in localizing and executing global enablement initiatives. You will report directly to a Senior Manager on the Global Sales Enablement team and support ANZ leadership through a dotted-line relationship with the local Sales Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be responsible for activating onboarding, training, and go-to-market programs that support the full sales lifecycle for sellers in ANZ. You’ll coordinate closely with Sales, Marketing, Product, and RevOps teams to ensure that enablement strategies are tailored to the regional context and drive measurable outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to help scale enablement across a high-growth region by aligning global frameworks with local needs and feedback..&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a hybrid role with three days per week in the office (Melbourne or Sydney) and two days remote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are excited about this opportunity because...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the &lt;strong&gt;execution&lt;/strong&gt; of onboarding, ongoing training, and product activation initiatives for DoorDash sales teams across &lt;strong&gt;Australia and New Zealand&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;liaison between global enablement&lt;/strong&gt; strategy and local sales execution, customizing programs for ANZ market needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner cross-functionally&lt;/strong&gt; with Sales, RevOps, Marketing, and Product teams to ensure readiness for product launches and sales plays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain and optimize regional enablement workflows including content delivery, sales tool adoption, and feedback loops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;culture of learning&lt;/strong&gt; by coordinating training calendars, facilitating sessions, and tracking engagement and outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather insights from frontline teams to help identify skill gaps and recommend enablement solutions that drive seller performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on enablement impact using available data and feedback to continuously improve delivery and relevance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-7&amp;nbsp; years of experience in &lt;strong&gt;sales enablement, sales operations, learning &amp;amp; development&lt;/strong&gt;, or a related go-to-market function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting sales organizations, preferably within a &lt;strong&gt;tech, SaaS, or marketplace environment&lt;/strong

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DoorDash Recruiting Team is focused on helping build DoorDash culture, one quality hire at a time. We partner with hiring teams to build recruiting strategies that allow DoorDash to hire remarkable talent in the most efficient and unbiased ways. This is a hybrid role, with 3 days a week in office, which can be located in Melbourne or Sydney.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At DoorDash, our Sourcers play an essential part in supporting our growing teams. They work alongside our recruiters and hiring managers while managing candidates at the top of the funnel. This is a unique and highly impactful opportunity to help accelerate the business by engaging qualified candidates across multiple business functions and acting as a subject matter expert and owner of market insights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note this role is a 6 month FTC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build partnerships with several of our business leaders across a range of teams (Sales, Strategy &amp;amp; Ops, Corporate Functions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the recruiters and hiring managers to develop creative strategies for engaging qualified candidates for their teams through resume screening, outbound sourcing, networking and referrals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help influence hiring decisions at each point in the recruiting process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data, your knowledge, and industry trends to build creative sourcing strategies and iterate on our interview process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 4 + years of sourcing experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have mastered successful pipeline management using an ATS, LinkedIn, and a variety of other channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You enjoy sourcing for unique roles and like to find needles in haystacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have outstanding written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re metrics driven - able to leverage data to help guide your decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
