&lt;p&gt;As one of DoorDash&#39;s core operations teams, Customer Experience and Support Operations, ensures that when there are bumps in the last mile, there&#39;s always someone there to help make things right. Our team designs and manages DoorDash&#39;s large and growing global network of support centers to create the best customer experiences, with the ultimate goal of delivering an outstanding customer experience as reliably as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Merchant Experience Partners to partner with our highest-value merchants to help solve their most pressing issues and provide the opportunity to improve their overall merchant experience as we continue to increase our last-mile logistics platform. &lt;br&gt;As a Merchant Experience Partner, you will play a crucial role within the Merchant Experience team by providing our merchants with a direct contact for all of their support needs and focusing your efforts on ensuring overall Merchant success on the DoorDash platform. You will build long-lasting relationships with our Merchants through excellent customer service and strategic problem-solving. &lt;br&gt;Not only will you partner with our Merchants, but you will work with Account Owners and own a book of business as their support contact. You will be a part of a&amp;nbsp; program to shape support as a differentiator in the marketplace through high-quality, white-glove service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and troubleshoot important issues for Merchants via phone and web&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with Merchant partners by being the main contact and expert for a portfolio of Merchants spanning Enterprise and small - medium businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote retention and overall Merchant success through white-glove service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily phone outreach to proactively resolve issues for Merchants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritise and escalate issues in partnership with our teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing conflicting deadlines, ensuring cross-functional collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a solutions-focussed mindset, promoting Merchant success above all else&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate and track Merchant feedback to inform updates to our products and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re excited about you because you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in Customer success, account management, customer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft suite / G-Suite&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience providing advisory and partnership-level support through both proactive and reactive interactions with customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience advocating for customer experience within a team or initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You love thinking about new opportunities for process improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 500&quot;&gt;Notice to Applicants for Jobs Located in NYC or Remote Jobs Associated With Office in NYC Only&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We use Covey as part of our hiring and/or promotional process for jobs in NYC and certain features may qualify it as an AEDT in NYC. As part of the hiring and/o

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Restaurant Acquisition team is the engine behind DoorDash’s growth across New Zealand. We identify, pitch, and sign new SMB restaurant partners, bringing the best local dining onto the platform and expanding selection for customers in every market we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Executive, you’ll be responsible for acquiring new SMB restaurant partners for DoorDash across New Zealand. You’ll own the full sales cycle: from prospecting and outreach to pitching, negotiating, and signing, building a strong pipeline of high-quality merchants that fuel marketplace growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working cross-functionally with Marketing, Operations, Customer Success, and Strategy teams, you’ll use market insights and competitive intelligence to win in your territory and convert top prospects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: this is a highly field-based role requiring travel across your region and, at times, wider travel across New Zealand, including overnight stays. Candidates must hold a valid full New Zealand driver licence and be comfortable with travel requirements that may vary based on business priorities and market needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hunt and close new restaurant partners: pitch and sign SMB restaurants, from iconic local favourites to exciting up-and-coming venues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own your patch: develop and execute a strategic acquisition plan that prioritises high-value prospects and closes selection gaps in key markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data to win: leverage market intelligence, competitive insights, and platform data to build compelling pitches and prioritise outreach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate objections and negotiate commercially: tailor proposals that demonstrate clear value, handle competitive pushback, and close deals that set partners up for long-term success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with Marketing, Operations, and Post-Sales teams to ensure a seamless merchant onboarding experience and strong speed to first order&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a market expert: stay across competitor activity, local dining trends, and merchant sentiment to inform your approach and feed insights back to the wider business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lift the team by sharing winning tactics, pipeline best practices, and helping those around you succeed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in B2B sales, business development, or new business acquisition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales targets and closing new business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong prospecting and pipeline management skills with a hunter mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial acumen with the ability to craft compelling value propositions and negotiate effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, confident communicator — equally persuasive on the phone, over email, and in person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in high-growth, fast-paced environments; competitive, adaptable, and solutions-focused&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine team player — collaborative by nature and committed to helping others win&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold a valid full Ne

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Restaurant Operations team within Merchant Strategy &amp;amp; Operations (Mx S&amp;amp;O) owns the operating engine that powers our restaurant marketplace across ANZ. We focus on Restaurant Reliability and Quality as core growth levers – making sure restaurants are online when they should be, integrated into the right tools (e.g. POS), and presented with accurate, high-quality content to customers. As DoorDash continues to scale, our merchant operations engine must grow in precision, efficiency, and adaptability so restaurants experience best-in-class execution from onboarding through to sustainable growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an energetic, detail-loving Senior Associate to lead key strategic initiatives and own 1–2 capital OKRs for the ANZ restaurant business, focused on platform reliability and POS penetration. You will be directly responsible for ensuring restaurants are online when they should be, have accurate and compelling photos and menus, and are increasingly integrated into reliable POS flows that unlock scalable growth and operational quality. You will also support the program management and leadership of our POS penetration program, driving adoption and impact across priority restaurant cohorts. This role is hybrid, with a minimum of 3 days in-office in Melbourne or Sydney.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own strategic Restaurant OKRs: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead the strategy, roadmap, and execution for &lt;strong&gt;1–2 capital OKRs&lt;/strong&gt; tied to ANZ restaurant platform reliability (e.g., uptime, menu accuracy, photo coverage), and be accountable for moving these metrics in a material way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be the DRI for platform reliability: &lt;/strong&gt;Act as the single-threaded owner for restaurant reliability across ANZ, ensuring stores are online when they should be, menus are accurate and reliable, and photo coverage meets a best-in-class bar for our customers and merchants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive our POS penetration program: &lt;/strong&gt;Support the &lt;strong&gt;program management and leadership&lt;/strong&gt; of our &lt;strong&gt;POS penetration program&lt;/strong&gt;, including defining target cohorts, building the rollout plan, tracking adoption and impact, and coordinating cross-functional execution with Sales, Integrations, and Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive complex, data-backed decision-making: &lt;/strong&gt;Use &lt;strong&gt;SQL&lt;/strong&gt; and internal data tools to run complex analyses, build decision frameworks, and separate signal from noise. You’ll quantify trade-offs, pressure-test ideas, and turn insights into clear recommendations and action plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leverage AI and automation to scale impact: &lt;/strong&gt;Use &lt;strong&gt;AI tools&lt;/strong&gt; to streamline repetitive analysis, monitoring, and documentation so you can spend more time on second- and third-order thinking, stakeholder engagement, and strategic ideation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape and operationalise new operating models: &lt;/strong&gt;Design and implement scalable playbooks, processes, and monitoring for key operational priorities, ensurin

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Go-To-Market (GTM) team within Merchant Strategy &amp;amp; Operations (Mx S&amp;amp;O) owns the operating engine that brings the right merchants onto DoorDash and sets them up for long-term success on the platform. Our Onboarding &amp;amp; Activation function sits at the heart of this — ensuring every new restaurant launches correctly and stays healthy from day one. From accurate menu descriptions and compelling photo coverage to correct trading hours and reliable POS integration, the quality of onboarding directly shapes both the merchant and consumer experience across ANZ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Associate to help scale and optimise quality across the Onboarding &amp;amp; Activation function, with a primary focus on menu operations. This role sits within the GTM team and works closely with Operations, Sales, Product, Integrations, and menu operations teams to drive quality at scale. You&#39;ll be accountable for defining what &quot;great&quot; looks like during onboarding and activation — and improving and optimising the frameworks, systems, and playbooks to get there consistently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help shape and execute the approach to menu accuracy across new and activating merchant cohorts:&lt;/strong&gt; Descriptions, item completeness, photo coverage, pricing accuracy, category structure, and platform compliance. Raise the quality bar on menu data to improve the merchant and consumer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive activation quality across Onboarding &amp;amp; Activation: &lt;/strong&gt;Work across the full activation suite to raise the baseline quality of every new merchant launch. Define what &quot;great&quot; looks like at activation and close the gap between signed and truly live.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage and monitor tools and technology across the Onboarding &amp;amp; Activation workstream&lt;/strong&gt;: Oversee the tools embedded in the merchant activation process — ensuring they&#39;re performing effectively, and continuously improving how this technology supports merchant quality at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improve and optimise the Early Merchant Success approach:&lt;/strong&gt; Track early merchant health signals, identify at-risk operators, and refine the interventions that drive platform engagement, uptime, and long-term retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead cross-functional initiatives:&lt;/strong&gt; Work with Sales to educate merchants before close, with Product &amp;amp; Integrations on tooling that unlocks better menu data quality, and with central operations teams on shared activation standards across ANZ.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turn data into action:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the analytics behind menu and activation quality — track metrics, diagnose root causes, and build the business case for initiatives. Use SQL and internal data tools to measure what&#39;s working and where to invest next.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have 3+ years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; across operations, strategy, analytics, or product

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://click.appcast.io/greenhouse-te8/a31.png?ent=34&amp;amp;e=22630&amp;amp;t=1701374353806&quot; width=&quot;1px&quot;&gt; &lt;img style=&quot;display: none; max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://track.jobadx.com/v1/i.gif?utm_pixel=224e990b-8ff4-4287-8d5d-2ff09647f181&amp;amp;utm_ptz=EST&amp;amp;utm_rqt=track&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New Verticals is a lean, high-impact team at DoorDash focused on shaping the future of local commerce beyond restaurants. We have ambitious goals to scale our International New Verticals business and drive our next wave of growth. We operate in a dynamic environment, solve interesting and ambiguous problems, and bring new customer experiences to market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Associate on the International New Verticals Strategy &amp;amp; Operations team, you will own developing our selection strategy for new &amp;amp; emerging business lines and leading commercial modelling for our negotiations across existing &amp;amp; new partnerships for Australia and New Zealand. You’ll support at key moments across the full cycle of a merchant including sizing TAM for new business segment, defining Sales lead list priorities, setting commercial rates, building out sales intelligence materials, supporting go-to-market efforts for new merchants, managing contractual commitments, supporting in re-negotiations, as well as so much more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a true mix of strategy &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; operations, combining strategic planning and analysis with hands-on operational execution. Reporting into the GM of New Verticals for ANZ, you will work cross-functionally with business development, account management, product, analytics, finance, and strategy &amp;amp; operations, while also individually driving key workstreams forward. The best candidates will be as excited by the higher-level strategic and cross-functional work as they are about the high-impact operational and execution components of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategise&lt;/strong&gt;. From first principles, you’ll develop and execute our selection strategy for new and existing business lines, ultimately making the case for which new category, sub category, or service we’ll launch on the platform next and how we’ll enter.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyse&lt;/strong&gt;. You’ll leverage advanced AI platforms in combination with traditional analytical skills to do detailed analysis that leverages data and learnings from our global organisation to help us determine where and how we should accelerate within existing verticals. You’ll assess the operational and financial impacts of our decisions, and iterate based on your analysis.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operate&lt;/strong&gt;. You’ll own tracking, execution, and iteration on the management of our commercial processes, ensuring we’re organised to tackle modelling every new deal, strategise for each renegotiation, and fully satisfy all contractual commitments. You’re excited to own your role, including everything from high-level strategy to nitty-gritty details.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicate. &lt;/strong&gt;You’ll help bridge the gap between strategy &amp;amp; operations and sales teams, ensuring each group understands and is working towards delivering on each other&#39;s top priorities. You’re a clear communicator and collaborator - you can explain what the numbers mean, align stakeholders, and turn insights into practical recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
