&lt;p&gt;DoorDash’s Legal team has built a strong reputation across the company for our collaborative, business-minded, and action-oriented approach to counseling. We are a diverse group of legal professionals passionate about delivering creative, practical, and best-in-class support to our business partners. We work closely with teams across the company to help accelerate and protect the business, while fostering a culture grounded in respect, trust, and continuous growth. Above all, we value being great teammates and are always looking for ways to learn and excel together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Senior Counsel to join DoorDash’s legal team in Australia. This role will serve as a key legal partner to the business, providing strategic, pragmatic advice across a wide range of legal and regulatory matters. As a generalist, you will support teams spanning strategy &amp;amp; operations, product, partnerships, and policy, helping to enable growth while managing risk in a dynamic and fast-evolving environment. You will report to the Senior Director of Litigation on our Global Legal team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a hybrid role based in Melbourne or Sydney, with three days per week in office and two days remote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operate as a generalist legal advisor &lt;/strong&gt;across a broad range of matters, including consumer law, regulatory compliance, commercial issues, litigation/investigations, and employment and contractor models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner closely with leaders&lt;/strong&gt; and subject matter experts across the global Legal team and collaborate cross-functionally with teams including operations, strategy, product, partnerships, and policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide pragmatic, business-oriented guidance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;on complex and evolving legal and regulatory issues impacting technology platforms and marketplace businesses across Australia and New Zealand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help navigate emerging regulatory and policy developments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;by delivering clear, actionable advice in fast-paced and often ambiguous environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build trusted relationships&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;across the business while developing scalable legal processes and frameworks, using strong judgment, integrity, and a solutions-oriented mindset to balance legal risk with business priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualified to practice law in Australia &lt;/strong&gt;with at least &lt;strong&gt;8+ years&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;PQE,&lt;/strong&gt; including experience advising on commercial, consumer, regulatory, and/or litigation matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;in-house experience &lt;/strong&gt;at a technology or other fast-paced international company preferred&lt;/li&gt;
