&lt;p&gt;DoorDash ANZ’s Integrated Marketing team is responsible for shaping how the brand shows up across Australia and New Zealand. Spanning strategy through to execution, the team brings together advertising, social and influencer, merchant co-marketing, partnerships, and local and Dasher marketing into one cohesive engine. Focused on customer-first thinking, the team creates campaigns that capture attention, build momentum, and embed DoorDash into culture in a highly competitive category.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;DoorDash ANZ is seeking a versatile and strategic Senior Manager to lead its Integrated Marketing function, owning the end-to-end strategy across Australia and New Zealand. This role will be responsible for aligning brand, growth, retention, merchant, and Dasher priorities into a cohesive, insight-led strategy that drives meaningful business outcomes and cultural impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This is a blended leadership, strategy, and execution role, requiring a hands-on operator who can connect long-term vision with day-to-day delivery. You will lead a high-performing team of 10 across Consumer and Partnerships Marketing and work closely with cross-functional stakeholders to drive alignment and impact across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Director of Marketing ANZ, you will play a critical role in shaping the Integrated Marketing function across ANZ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hybrid role, with 3 days in-office and 2 days remote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re excited about this opportunity because you will…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;72&quot; data-end=&quot;308&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;72&quot; data-end=&quot;115&quot;&gt;Lead the Integrated Marketing Function:&lt;/strong&gt; Inspire and develop a high-performing team, providing clear direction on vision, priorities, and execution while fostering a culture of continuous improvement, collaboration, and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;72&quot; data-end=&quot;308&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set the Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;: Define a customer-first, insight-led marketing strategy across Customer and Dasher audiences, making clear trade-offs to balance long-term brand building with short-term performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive High-Impact Campaigns&lt;/strong&gt;: Lead the development of cohesive, multi-channel campaigns that translate business priorities into culturally resonant, high-impact go-to-market executions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure Integration &amp;amp; Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;: Orchestrate cross-functional alignment, ensuring campaigns are consistent, scalable, and continuously optimised through learnings, reporting, and playbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leverage Partnerships for Growth&lt;/strong&gt;: Oversee co-marketing and partnerships to amplify reach and relevance, harnessing DoorDash’s merchant and partner ecosystem to drive incremental impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re excited about you because…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12+ years of integrated marketing experience &lt;/strong&gt;across in-house and agency environments, with bonus experience

